\begin_inset Formula $n_{0}$
\end_inset

 taki, że 
\begin_inset Formula $\forall n\geq n_{0}$
\end_inset

 zachodzi 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{n}(x_{0})>f(x_{0})+2\epsilon_{0}$
\end_inset

.
 Zatem dla każdego 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon<\epsilon_{0}$
\end_inset

 i 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in(x_{0},x_{0}+\delta)$
\end_inset

, gdzie 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

 jest tak wybrana, żeby 
\begin_inset Formula $|f(x)-f(x_{0})|\leq\epsilon_{0}$
\end_inset

, zachodzi 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{n}(x)\geq f_{n}(x_{0})>f(x_{0})+2\epsilon_{0}\geq f(x)+2\epsilon_{0}-\epsilon\geq f(x)+\epsilon$
\end_inset

.
 Zatem 
\begin_inset Formula $\underset{\epsilon\rightarrow0}{\lim}\underset{n\rightarrow\infty}{\lim}l^{1}\{x:f_{n}(x)-f(x)>\epsilon\}\geq\delta>0$
\end_inset

 
